  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>        A bit of jargon we won't use this semester, but can lead you down a rabbit hole if you want: when a rule and a proof system are like this---adding the rule to the proof system doesn't change the resulting logic---the rule is called <html:strong>admissible</html:strong> in the proof system.
        To say that the logics determined by NM, NJ, and NK are all different, then, is to say that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\bot  E]]></fr:tex> is not admissible in NM, and LEM is not admissible in NJ.</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
